Product Usage Tips

1. Main and Secondary Speakers
• Each speaker can be used individually as a main speaker (blue light) and connected to different
Bluetooth devices.
• To play multiple speakers in sync, set one speaker as the main speaker (blue light) and the others as secondary speakers (red light).

2. Switching Speaker Modes
• Press the Speaker Sync button on the remote to switch a speaker to a secondary speaker (red light).
• Press the Bluetooth Pairing button on the remote to switch a speaker to a main speaker (blue light).
• Restart the speaker after switching to ensure a stable connection.

3. Remote Control Functions
• All remote functions work only with the main speaker (blue light).
• Secondary speakers respond only to the Power and Bluetooth Pairing buttons.

4. Distance and Connection Stability
• The maximum distance between a Bluetooth device and the main speaker is 50 ft (~15 meters).
• The maximum distance between a main speaker and a secondary speaker is 100 ft (~30 meters).
• To avoid interference, maintain a minimum distance of 6 ft (~2 meters) between any two speakers and ensure there are no obstacles between them.

5. About Audio Delay
• Due to Bluetooth technology, audio may experience slight delays, which can cause sound and video to be out of sync.
• Our speakers are not recommended for TV use.

6. Volume and Environmental Tips
• If the volume is too low, increase the volume on both your Bluetooth device and the remote.
• Speaker volume is also affected by the environment. Large spaces may require multiple speakers to maintain optimal sound quality.

Recommended Troubleshooting Guide

Speaker Does Not Power On
Step 1: Verify Power Connection
•Confirm that the power adapter is securely connected to the speaker and wall outlet.
•Verify that the outlet is functioning properly.
Step 2: Power On Using Remote Control
•After power has been disconnected, the speaker must be turned on using the remote control.
•Each speaker must be powered on individually.
•The speaker will not automatically turn on after reconnecting power.
Step 3: Check Indicator Light
•Blue indicator: Main Speaker
•Red indicator: Secondary Speaker
If no indicator light appears after completing the above steps, please contact customer support for further assistance.

Bluetooth Connection Troubleshooting
Step 1: Remove Previous Pairings
Delete all devices named:
“Sync Speaker”
from the Bluetooth list of the mobile device.
Step 2: Configure Speaker Roles

To enable synchronized playback:
1.Select one speaker as the Main Speaker (Blue Indicator).
2.Set all other speakers as Secondary Speakers (Red Indicator).

Network Setup Sequence:
•Press Network Key on Main Speaker
•Press Network Key on Secondary Speaker

Bluetooth Pairing Sequence:
•Press Bluetooth Pairing Key on Secondary Speaker
•Press Bluetooth Pairing Key on Main Speaker
Step 3: Reconnect Bluetooth
Reconnect the mobile device to:
“Sync Speaker”
and verify audio playback.

Important Product Information

AC Powered Speakers
•These speakers require continuous AC power.
•They are not battery-powered speakers.
•A power adapter must remain connected during operation.

Independent Speaker Operation
•Each speaker can operate independently as a standalone Bluetooth speaker.
•Speakers do not need to be grouped to play audio.

Multi-Speaker Synchronization
For synchronized playback:
•One speaker must be configured as the Main Speaker (Blue Indicator).
•Additional speakers must be configured as Secondary Speakers (Red Indicator).
•Multiple speakers can then play the same audio simultaneously.
Power-On Behavior
•After power is disconnected or restored, speakers do not automatically power on.
•Each speaker must be turned on individually using the remote control.



